1.what is k8s?
Kubernetes (K8s) is an open-source container orchestration platform that manages containerized applications. It automates deployment, scaling,
and operations by providing features such as auto-scaling, 
self-healing, rolling updates, and automatic rollbacks, making applications easier to deploy and manage.
____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
what is docekr swarm?
Docker Swarm is a Docker orchestration platform that manages containerized applications across a cluster,
providing scaling, load balancing, and high availability.
__________________________________________________________________________________________-
what is d/f b/w k8s & docker swarm

Kubernetes (K8s) is an open source container orchestration platform that manages containerized applications. with advanced features like auto-scaling, 
self-healing, and a rich ecosystem.
Docker Swarm is Dockerâ€™s orchestration tool that is easy to set up and manage but it provides limited features. compared to k8s, 
Docker swarm lacks in auto scaling & automatic rollbacks which can be performed in the k8s easily
Kubernetes is the industry standard, while Docker Swarm is mainly used for smaller or simpler applications.



